{ Example: modify an XML document

  The follwing simple → Windows/PowerShell/script[PowerShell script] tries to demonstrate how an → development/XML/DOM/nodes/document can be modifed using `System.Xml.XmlDocument`:
  gh|.NET-API|/System/Xml/XmlDocument/_modify/modify.ps1||

  { orig.xml

    This is the `orig.xml` file that is modified by the script:
    gh|.NET-API|/System/Xml/XmlDocument/_modify/orig.xml||

  }
  { modified.xml

    The result of running the script is:
code {
<rt>
  <item id="foo">
    <valOne>foo 1</valOne>
    <valTwo>foo 2</valTwo>
  </item>
  <item id="baz">
    <valOne>baz 1</valOne>
    <valTwo>created</valTwo>
  </item>
  <elem id="bar">
    <valOne>created</valOne>
    <valTwo>created</valTwo>
  </elem>
</rt>
code }

  }
}

sa:

  The → Windows/PowerShell/language/object/type/accelerators[PowerShell type accelerator] for `System.Xml.XmlDocument` is `[xml]`.
